  "text_preview": "\"nice\" / \"clean\" - American Sign Language ASL University ► American Sign Language: \"nice / clean\" The sign for \"nice\" or \"clean\" is made by placing your left hand in front of you, palm up and moving the flat palm of your right hand across your left hand. (If you are right handed). \"Nice to meet you.\" Question: Are \"CLEAN\" and \"NICE\" the same sign? Answer: Yes, they are signed the same way. The concept \"is clean\" is signed the same way as the sign NICE. \"clean\" = NICE: See: animation \"nice / clean\" However, the concepts \"clean up,\" \"to clean,\" or \"cleaning\" use what I call \"the process\" form of the sign wherein you use extra movement to show a process is taking place. So, if you want to sign \"clean-up\" as in \"clean up your bedroom\" you would use a double motion. (Repeat the sign to mean: \"c"
}
